"```sparql\nPREFIX pbn: <https://github.com/mm80843/T3.5/raw/main/pbn_t3_5.owl#>\n\nSELECT (COUNT(DISTINCT ?class) as ?numClasses)\nWHERE {\n  ?class a owl:Class .\n  FILTER(STRSTARTS(STR(?class), STR(pbn:)))\n}\n```\n\nIn this SPARQL request, I am utilizing the `PREFIX` statement to define the namespace prefix `pbn` for the ontology namespace `https://github.com/mm80843/T3.5/raw/main/pbn_t3_5.owl#`. \n\nNext, I am using the `SELECT` clause to count the number of distinct classes in the ontology. I am using the `COUNT` function to count the number of distinct classes and aliasing the result as `numClasses`. \n\nIn the `WHERE` clause, I am querying for ?class instances that are of type `owl:Class` and filtering only those classes that start with the namespace `pbn`. \n\nThis request will count the number of distinct classes in the ontology that are defined within the specified namespace."